text: Jaroslav Jeřábek (born 2 April 1971) is a Slovak former cyclist. He competed for Czechoslovakia at the 1992 Summer Olympics and for Slovakia at the 2000 Summer Olympics and the 2004 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak male cyclists Category:Olympic cyclists of Czechoslovakia Category:Olympic cyclists of Slovakia Category:Cyclists at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Cyclists at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:Cyclists at the 2004 Summer Olympics Category:People from Louny
